<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-17T11:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-17T11:45:00-05:00" n="865" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d865">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/7629: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HME1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-17T11:00:00-05:45">November
                                    17, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 5:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>214. Department’s 118, November 16, 1 p.m. The governing boards of the
                            two major parties ratified the agreements and are now taking preliminary
                            steps to place them into effect. Text of agreements will go forward by
                            air mail Saturday.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HME1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>